Earlier this year , <COREF ID="2" TYPE="IDENT">Cordis , a maker of medical devices ,</COREF> agreed to plead guilty to felony and misdemeanor charges related to <COREF ID="3" TYPE="IDENT">the pacemakers</COREF> and to pay the government about $ 5.7 million in fines and other costs .
<COREF ID="2" TYPE="IDENT">Cordis</COREF> sold <COREF ID="2" TYPE="IDENT">its</COREF> pacemaker operations two years ago to Telectronics Holding Ltd. of Australia .
